name: addr2line::SplitDwarfLoad
doc_adt:
This struct contains the information needed to find split DWARF data
 and to produce a `gimli::Dwarf<R>` for it.

VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(0)).name: dwo_id
VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(0)).doc:
The dwo id, for looking up in a DWARF package, or for
 verifying an unpacked dwo found on the file system

VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(1)).name: comp_dir
VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(1)).doc: The compilation directory `path` is relative to.

VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(2)).name: path
VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(2)).doc: A path on the filesystem, relative to `comp_dir` to find this dwo.

VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(3)).name: parent
VariantIdx(None)-FieldIdx(Some(3)).doc:
Once the split DWARF data is loaded, the loader is expected
 to call [make_dwo(parent)](gimli::read::Dwarf::make_dwo) before
 returning the data.
